    • Constructor Detail

      • Project

        public Project(java.lang.String name,
               java.lang.String id,
               int intPriority,
               ImprovementCollaborator leader,
               Request approvedRequest)

        Project

        Description: Constructs a new Project object with the specified name, ID, priority, leader, and approved request. The priority of the project is set changing the selected int to a priority level using Priority.intToPriority(int). Then, utilizing the classification date extracted from the approvedReques using Request.getClassificationDate(), and the intPriority option selected, an estimated close date is calculated (calcEstCloseDate(Calendar, int)). Finally, the related request realted to the project is saved inside the project too.

        Preconditions:

        • The name parameter must be a String representing the name of the project.
        • The id parameter must be a String representing the ID of the project.
        • The intPriority parameter must be an integer representing the priority of the project (1 for urgent, 2 for high, 3 for medium, and 4 for low).
        • The leader parameter must be an ImprovementCollaborator object representing the leader of the project.
        • The approvedRequest parameter must be a Request object representing the approved request associated with the project.

        Postconditions:

        • A new Project object is created with the provided name, ID, priority, leader, and approved request.
        • The project priority is set using the Priority.intToPriority(int) method to change the int option to an actual Priority level.
        • The classification date of the project is set to the classification date of the approved request, obtained using the Request.getClassificationDate() method.
        • The estimated close date of the project is calculated based on its classification date and priority, using the calcEstCloseDate(Calendar, int) method.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the project.
        id - The ID of the project.
        intPriority - The priority of the project (1 for urgent, 2 for high, 3 for medium, and 4 for low).
        leader - The leader of the project.
        approvedRequest - The approved request associated with the project.

      • calcEstCloseDate

        public static java.util.Calendar calcEstCloseDate(java.util.Calendar classificationDate,
                                                  int intPriority)

        calcEstCloseDate

        Description: Calculates the estimated close date of a project based on its classification date and priority.
        • intPriority 1 = Urgent. It must be delivered in less than 5 days
        • intPriority 2 = High. It must be delivered in less than 10 days
        • intPriority 3 = Medium. It must be delivered in less than 30 days
        • intPriority 4 = Low. It must be delivered in less than 60 days

        Preconditions:

        • The classificationDate parameter must be a Calendar object representing the classification date of the accepted request.
        • The intPriority parameter must be an integer representing the priority of the project (int between1 and 4).

        Postconditions:

        • The estimated close date of the project is calculated based on its classification date and priority.
        Parameters:
        classificationDate - The classification date of the accepted request.
        intPriority - The priority of the project (1 for urgent, 2 for high, 3 for medium, and 4 for low).
        Returns:
        The estimated close date of the project.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()

        toString

        Description: Generates a string representation of the project, including its details such as name, ID, priority level, leader, registration date, estimated close date, end date, and approved request information. Not only will the method return the basic information of the project but it will access specifics of the leader (Collaborator.getFullName() and Collaborator.getId()}) and display all the info request the project is related to (Request.toString()).

        Preconditions:

        • The classification date, estimated close date must be initialized Calendar objects.
        • If the project has been closed, the end date must not be null.
        • The leader must be initialized.
        • The priority level and approved request must be initialized and contain valid information.

        Postconditions:

        • Returns a string representation of the project, including its details.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        A string representation of the project.

      • calculateEfficiency

        public double calculateEfficiency()
        Calculates and returns the efficiency of the project based on the deviation between the estimated close date and the actual close date. The efficiency is calculated using the following formula: 
             Efficiency = 1 - (Difference in days / 100)
        Where:
        • Difference in days is the difference in days between the estimated close date and the actual close date.
        • Efficiency represents the efficiency of the project, expressed as a percentage.
        A higher efficiency value indicates that the project was completed closer to its estimated close date, while a lower efficiency value indicates a greater deviation from the estimated close date.
        Specified by:
        calculateEfficiency in interface EfficiencyCalculable
        Returns:
        The efficiency of the project, expressed as a percentage.
